07/01/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Foreign Minister Mircea Geoana said Monday (6 January) that the government is poised to launch the second and most decisive round of NATO membership negotiations in Brussels. Thursday's talks will focus on protection of classified information and on legislative adjustments. According to NATO's step-by-step membership plan for the seven newly-invited countries, the membership process should be completed by May 2004 at the latest.
In other news, Romanian EU Integration Minister Vasile Puscas predicted over the weekend that the country would introduce the euro as an official currency in 2009 or 2010 - two to three years after Romania's expected entry into the EU. (Rompres, Radio Romania, Mediafax, Pari - 06/01/03)
